    "descriptions": {
      "short": "Erlang/OTP - for building concurrent, distributed, and fault tolerant systems",
      "long": "OTP is a set of Erlang libraries, which consists of the Erlang runtime system, a number of ready-to-use components mainly written in Erlang, and a set of design principles for Erlang programs. Features Concurrency - Lightweight processes with message passing Distribution - Built-in support for distributed systems Fault Tolerance - Supervision trees and hot code swapping Soft Real-Time - Predictable low-latency response times High Availability - Design for systems that never stop Use Cases Erlang is used in telecoms, banking, e-commerce, instant messaging, and any system requiring high availability and scalability. Learn more at erlang.org.",
      "source": "choco",
      "homepage": "http://www.erlang.org/",
      "lastUpdatedAt": "2026-06-11T04:59:21.010Z"
    },
